President Donald J. Trump has announced his second wave of United States Marshal nominations. The United States Marshal is responsible for protecting the Federal judiciary, apprehending fugitives, transporting prisoners, and protecting witnesses. The six candidates nominated by President Trump are Frank M. Coffman for the Eastern District of Oklahoma, Thomas M. Griffin, Jr. for the District of South Carolina, Mark S. James for the Western District of Missouri, Johnny Lee Kuhlman for the Western District of Oklahoma, Daniel C. Mosteller for the District of South Dakota, and Gary G. Schofield for the District of Nevada. These individuals have backgrounds in law enforcement and security, and if confirmed, they will serve as United States Marshals for their respective jurisdictions.